<p>When I save a User model, I would like to check if it has a username. Therefore I wrote this <code>pre_save</code>:</p>  <pre><code>@receiver(pre_save, sender=User) def validate_user(sender, instance, **kwargs):     if len(instance.username) &lt;= 5: raise Exception("Username too short") </code></pre>  <p>Now in my testing method I would like to test this exception:</p>  <pre><code>def test_user_no_username(self):     u = User.objects.create()     self.assertRaises(Exception, u.save()) </code></pre>  <p>The test fails. Why?</p>